fehd.ADR_EN: LG/F, 75-75A HOLLYWOOD ROAD, CENTRAL, HONG KONG
fehd.ADR_TC: 香港中環荷李活道75-75號A地下低層

result.adr_address: 75 Hollywood Rd, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Les Fils à Maman

reviews.text:
Great French Place. Everything I tried tasted authentic like back home! 
For example, Steak frites are as good (if not better) as a Brasserie in Paris !

Lovely little rustic french restaurant tucked away from the crowds. Daily specials at reasonable prices for the area and excellent quality of the food. Had a delicious duck confit for lunch. Nice wine list by the glass. Excellent service - highly recommend!

A complete sham. Outrageous prices for amateur French food at best. French people doing food under a French name doesn't necessarily make it good food. Go for the bar where they didn't do anything more than add ice or water. You are wasting your time and calorie quota otherwise. Scandaleux.

If you like French home cooking, this is the restaurant to go to. It’s in a quiet little area off Hollywood Street in Soho. Good place for a nice Sunday brunch over wine. The Cote de Boeuf was excellent for sharing and the manager there was super friendly.

Superbe spot! I landed in HK and saw its reviews and was not disappointed.

Super friendly and helpful Stephane guides me through both the food and wine menu, had a good laugh and sure to recommend/hit this spot again very soon!

A little piece of France in a busy city 🇭🇰
